# X Platform – AI Assistant System Documentation

## Project Overview

X Platform is an advanced e-learning platform designed initially for Jordanian Tawjihi students.

The platform supports:

- Students
- Teachers
- Admins

The system currently includes:

- Authentication and Security System
- Courses and Lessons
- Video Protection and Session Control
- Internal Purchase System
- Access Codes
- Video Streaming Integration
- AI Assistant System

The AI Assistant was designed to become a course-specific educational assistant that helps students understand course material while remaining fully restricted to the scientific content provided by the course creator.

---

# AI Assistant System Overview

The platform now includes a fully integrated AI Assistant system.

The assistant:

- Works only inside purchased courses
- Uses only the course material provided by the teacher/admin
- Refuses unrelated questions
- Generates:
  - Answers
  - Quizzes
  - Exercises
  - Examples

- Logs AI usage and token consumption
- Supports scientific material uploads through files

The system was intentionally designed to support future RAG upgrades without rebuilding the architecture.

---

# AI Assistant Goals

The AI Assistant system was designed with several important goals:

## Educational Restriction

The assistant must answer ONLY using the course material.

It must NOT:

- Use unrelated knowledge
- Answer questions outside the course
- Use information from other courses
- Generate fabricated information

---

## Cost Protection

The platform owner should not pay AI costs for unauthorized users.

Therefore:

- Only enrolled students can access the assistant
- Teachers can access their own course assistant
- Admins can access all assistants

---

## Future Scalability

The architecture was designed to later support:

- RAG
- Vector databases
- Semantic search
- Embeddings
- AI memory systems
- Analytics

without rebuilding the assistant from scratch.

